Make the UserDefaults removal synchronous with the cache clear. The simplest approach: call safeWrite synchronously for clear operations, or update the cache to the known-empty state directly (bypassing defaults) so a read never falls through to stale UserDefaults data. For example, in clearExamHistory:

func clearExamHistory() {
    _examHistoryCache = []          // set known-empty before removing from defaults
    _completedExamSetsCache = []
    safeWrite {
        $0.removeObject(forKey: Keys.examHistory)
        $0.removeObject(forKey: Keys.completedExamSets)
    }
    _readinessCache = nil
    _smartNudgeCache = nil
}

Apply the same pattern to all other clear* functions: set the cache to the known post-clear value ([] or empty Set()) before (or instead of) calling invalidateCaches(), so the next read hits the already-correct cache rather than falling through to stale defaults.

